evidence: Nonlinear science is a relatively new and complex area.
Unlike linear systems, nonlinear equations are often difficult, or even impossible, to solve exactly.
But thanks to modern computing, we can discretize these equations and compute solutions numerically-even if we have to do so through brute force.
Nonlinear systems are fascinating because they produce surprising, often counterintuitive phenomena.
